  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Combine</strong> the dried dill, half of the mustard &amp; 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(6 tbsp)</span> of olive oil in a large mixing bowl</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> with 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> (1 tsp)</span> of salt and plenty of pepper to your taste</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the pork loin steaks, coat evenly and set aside</p>\r\n<p><strong>Prepare</strong> 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">(4)</span> A4 size pieces of clingfilm</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Lay</strong> the pork loin steaks on top of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">(2)</span> piece<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> of clingfilm, with ample space between them</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> any left over mustard mixture on top of each steak</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cover</strong> the steaks with the remaining cling film&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bash</strong> with the bottom of a spare pot or rolling pin to 1 1/2cm thickness and set aside until step 5</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> the parsnips, cut in half lengthways and chop into pieces (approx. 1cm)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the parsnip and a pinch of salt (optional) to a pot of boiling water and boil for 10-15 min or until you can pierce them easily with a fork</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, grate the cheddar</p>\r\n<p><strong>Crush</strong>, peel and chop (or grate) the garlic finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tear</strong> the cavolo nero leaves from the tough inner stalk and discard the stalks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Roll</strong> or bunch up the leaves and cut into bite-size pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> 1-2 tbsp of olive oil to a pan on a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> the oil is hot, hold the strip of fat from the pork steaks against the pan, keeping them steady with tongs for 1 min, or until the fat is melted and golden brown</p>\r\n<p><strong>Then</strong> lay the steaks flat and cook for 3 min on each side or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove</strong> the pork steaks from the pan, cover and leave to rest for 5 min, reserving the pan for step 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Drain</strong> and return the cooked parsnip to the cooking pot, add 1-2 tbsp of butter, a splash of milk, the remaining mustard and the grated cheese</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mash</strong> and season to your taste with salt and pepper, then cover until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Return</strong> the reserved pan to a medium heat and add 1-2 tbsp of olive oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the garlic and cook for 30 sec, stirring constantly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the cavolo nero and lower the heat to low</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> up to 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(300ml)</span> of water and cook for 3-4 min or until wilted and tender</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> any resting juices from the meat and mix through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/120.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong> the pork over the parsnip mash, with the cavolo nero to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
